    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "OMG it's a mess. \r\n\r\nI'm really unsure how to do it without changing tons of API to pass results around without changing the bowels of IPython behaves. Unless we accept that IPython shows extra stacktraces for run that show the inside of IPython, in which case it's just a matter of changing tests. \r\n\r\n@takluyver is there a way to re-raise omitting some stacks ?  We could do that (or generally add an option to IPython's showtraceback that skip traceback internal frames?)"
  },
