    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yeah, I think I suspected that this one was going to be tricky, and that's why I hadn't tried to fix it.\r\n\r\nWe have `UsageError` which magics can raise to fail with a one-line message rather than a full traceback. Maybe we should add an exception type like `SilentError` which they can use to indicate failure when they have already taken care of displaying the error details."
